<p><strong>Two features you might have missed</strong></p>

<p>recuerd0 does more than store text. Here are two capabilities worth knowing about.</p>

<p><strong>1. FTS5 search operators</strong></p>

<p>The API supports full SQLite FTS5 syntax. A few examples:</p>

<pre style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 6px; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 14px; overflow-x: auto;"># Exact phrase
recuerd0 search '"deployment config"' --pretty

# Boolean operators
recuerd0 search 'rails AND deployment NOT staging' --pretty

# Column filters
recuerd0 search 'title:architecture' --pretty</pre>

<p>This is especially useful when your AI tools query recuerd0 — they can write precise queries to find exactly the context they need.</p>

<p><strong>2. Memory versioning</strong></p>

<p>Every time you update a memory, recuerd0 saves the previous version. You can view the full history and compare changes — nothing is ever lost.</p>

<p>This means your AI tools can safely update shared project context. If something goes wrong, you can always roll back.</p>

